<a name="2640"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">CNET Keeps You Connected to CES</div>
<br />
<A href="http://www.cnet.com/ces" target=_blank><IMG height=99 hspace=8 src="/print/images/content/CNET-logo.jpg" width=95 align=left border=0></A>CNET, where people go to discover the latest in tech and consumer electronics, will be all over the 2009 CES!&nbsp; In addition to broadcasting from the CNET Live Stage, CNET will host Car Tech with a satellite stage in the LVCC, North Hall (booth #2416) where the CNET Car Tech expert editors conduct interviews with after-market car accessory vendors and installation demos throughout the show. But that’s not all. Not even close.<BR><BR>CNET will also host the 4th Annual <A href="/print/awards/bestOfCES.asp">Best of CES Awards</A>. This fierce competition recognizes the best new products in 10 categories, plus Best in Show and People’s Voice. Be a part of it at the CNET Live Stage in the LVCC, South Hall 3 Lobby: Finalists will be announced 10 a.m. Friday, January 9. Winners will be announced 11 a.m. Saturday, January 10. And don’t miss <A href="/print/sessions/SuperSessions.asp">CNET’s Next Big Thing SuperSession</A>, a standing-room-only event where Brian Cooley and a team of expert editors reveal the big trends and emerging categories for 2009. It all happens 3 p.m. Thursday, January 8 in the LVCC, North Hall, N255-N257. <BR><BR>For CNET's in-depth coverage leading up to the show, visit <A href="http://www.cnet.com/ces" target=_blank>www.cnet.com/ces</A>.

